{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 11:58:13.997928", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Connectivity problem**\\n\\nThe ping tests from `host_1_1_1_1` to both the DNS server (`10.200.0.2`) and the server‑access router (`10.200.0.1`) timed out, and the reverse pings also timed out.  \\nThis indicates that the host cannot reach the network that contains the DNS server or the server‑access router.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n`host_1_1_1_1` is configured with:\\n\\n```\\ndefault via 10.1.1.1 dev eth0\\n```\\n\\nbut **no interface in the topology has the address 10.1.1.1**.  \\nThe server‑access router has 10.200.0.1 on `br0` and 172.16.0.11 on `eth7`; the DNS server has 10.200.0.2 on `eth0`.  \\nBecause the host’s default gateway is wrong, all packets destined for 10.200.0.0/24 (and any other non‑local subnet) are sent to a non‑existent gateway, so they never leave the host.\\n\\n**Resulting symptoms**\\n\\n* Ping to `10.200.0.2` (DNS) – timeout  \\n* Ping to `10.200.0.1` (server‑access router) – timeout  \\n* Ping from the server‑access router back to the host – timeout  \\n\\n**Fix**\\n\\nCorrect the host’s default gateway to the IP address of the router that actually connects it to the 10.200.0.0/24 network (e.g., `10.200.0.1` or whatever the correct gateway is). Once the default gateway is fixed, the host will be able to reach the DNS server and the server‑access router, restoring connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='7bb69a2d-d472-4eac-b468-a7e98a2fbd1f'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
